From 4fce6f28e74555aee3b5ee0c7736ab01f27b623a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Max Furman <taygoth@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 00:19:42 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 2/9] Input: touchscreen/stm/ftm5: request IRQ with NO_AUTOEN

`request_threaded_irq()` enables the interrupt as soon as the handler
is installed. On the FTM5 driver this happens before
`fts_chip_powercycle()` has finished bringing the controller up: a
race where the controller fires an early edge before the host has
finished configuring `IRQF_TRIGGER_LOW` polarity can lead to IRQ storm
and a wedged controller (observed reliably on Mi 8 / dipper).

Pass `IRQF_NO_AUTOEN` so the IRQ stays masked until the driver itself
calls `fts_enableInterrupt()` during sensing initialization.

The previously-commented call hints that the intended sequence already
was "enable IRQ after powercycle"; this patch makes that explicit and
race-free.

Signed-off-by: Max Furman <taygoth@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/input/touchscreen/stm/fts.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/input/touchscreen/stm/fts.c b/drivers/input/touchscreen/stm/fts.c
index 8e35cf7a4..05d4510a6 100644
--- a/drivers/input/touchscreen/stm/fts.c
+++ b/drivers/input/touchscreen/stm/fts.c
@@ -3484,7 +3484,7 @@ static int fts_interrupt_install(struct fts_ts_info *info)
 	}
 
 	error = request_threaded_irq(info->client->irq, fts_isr,
-			fts_interrupt_handler, IRQF_ONESHOT | IRQF_TRIGGER_LOW,
+			fts_interrupt_handler, IRQF_ONESHOT | IRQF_TRIGGER_LOW | IRQF_NO_AUTOEN,
 			FTS_TS_DRV_NAME, info);
 
 	if (error) {
@@ -3628,7 +3628,7 @@ static int fts_init_sensing(struct fts_ts_info *info)
 
 	error |= fts_mode_handler(info, 0);	/* enable the features and
 						 * sensing */
-	/* error |= fts_enableInterrupt(); */	/* enable the interrupt */
+	error |= fts_enableInterrupt();	/* enable the interrupt */
 	error |= fts_resetDisableIrqCount();
 
 	if (error < OK)
